  "text": "In spite of more than 10 years of routine use of PITC RP-HPLC in clinical amino acid analysis, validation data for its urine application are scant [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A linear response up to 2 mmol/L has been demonstrated as well as a 10-fold increase in sensitivity compared with ninhydrin methods [CITATION_3] , with even greater sensitivity and higher linear responses for non-␣-amino acids such as imino acids and ␤-amino acids. Likewise, Ͼ100 compounds and pharmacological metabolites have been comprehensively studied as potential interferents [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
